pr_title: Setup.py Fails because certain needs to be installed manually
pr_body:
<!--- Provide a general, concise summary of your changes in the Title above -->
On running `python setup.py develop` a ModuleNotFoundError is thrown, due to which the installation process fails.
The reason being `"from owtf import __version"` imports packages from `install_requires dependencies `which are not yet installed
We have to manually install the following Modules Tornado, PyYAML, Six, and then run `python setup.py develop` again to complete the installation process.

## Description
<!--- Describe your changes in detail -->
Instead of importing the version number, the code the version will now extract it from init.py

## Related Issue
<!--- This project only accepts pull requests related to open issues -->
<!--- If suggesting a new feature or change, please discuss it in an issue first -->
<!--- If fixing a bug, there should be an issue describing it with steps to reproduce -->
<!--- Please link to the issue here: -->
https://github.com/owtf/owtf/issues/1057

## Motivation and Context
<!--- Why is this change required? What problem does it solve? -->
To install OWTF, without the user manually needing to install the required dependent modules.

## Reviewers
<!--- @mentions of the person/people responsible for reviewing proposed changes. -->
@viyatb @sharmamohit123 


## Types of changes
<!--- What types of changes does your code introduce? Put an `x` in all the boxes that apply: -->

<!--- If you're unsure about any of these, don't hesitate to ask. We're here to help! -->
- [X] My code follows the code style (modified PEP8) of this project.

<!--- Provide a general, concise summary of your changes in the Title above -->

- Using python3.7 to run OWTF, since python3.8 had dependency issues. 
- Changed creation and activation of Python Virtual Environment.
- Added wait-for-it.sh which was missing in Docker folder.
- Updated configuration in settings.py to connect with PostgreSQL container.
- Changed Kali Linux image to kalilinux/kali.

pr_title: Fix#1069 Ensures that only selected plugins run
pr_body:
<!--- Provide a general, concise summary of your changes in the Title above -->
On selecting a particular plugin to run, all plugins were automatically getting selected and running,

## Description
<!--- Describe your changes in detail -->

1. Sending the data as plugin_data.

_Before the change_
`0=g&1=r&2=o&3=u&4=p&5=%3D&6=w&7=e&8=b&9=%26&10=t&11=y&12=p&13=e&14=%3D&15=s&16=e&17=m&18=i&19=_&20=p&21=a&22=s&23=s&24=i&25=v&26=e&27=%26&28=c&29=o&30=d&31=e&32=%3D&33=O&34=W&35=T&36=F&37=&38=I&39=G&40=&41=0&42=0&43=4&44=%26&45=i&46=d&47=%3D&48=1&49=2&50=%26&51=f&52=o&53=r&54=c&55=e&56=_&57=o&58=v&59=e&60=r&61=w&62=r&63=i&64=t&65=e&66=%3D&67=f&68=a&69=l&70=s&71=e`

_After the change_
`plugin_data: group=web&type=semi_passive&code=OWTF-IG-004&id=4&force_overwrite=false`

2. Convert all self.request.arguments from byte to character (Unicode) string.

_Before the change_
{'plugin_data': [b'group=web&type=semi_passive&code=OWTF-IG-004&id=5&force_overwrite=false']}

_After the change_
{'plugin_data': ['group=web&type=semi_passive&code=OWTF-IG-004&id=5&force_overwrite=false']}

3.  Parse the data in required format by filter_data in post()

_Before the change_
{'plugin_data': ['group=web&type=semi_passive&code=OWTF-IG-004&id=7&force_overwrite=false']

_After the change_
{'group': ['web'], 'type': ['semi_passive'], 'code': ['OWTF-IG-004'], 'id': ['10'], 'force_overwrite': ['false

## Related Issue
<!--- This project only accepts pull requests related to open issues -->
<!--- If suggesting a new feature or change, please discuss it in an issue first -->

pr_body:
On Running OWTF-CM-003 Infrastructure Configuration Management, File "HTTP-Traceroute.py" throws various errors.
1. NameError: name 'urllib' is not defined
2. AttributeError: type object 'Request' has no attribute 'build_opener' etc

## Description
<!--- Describe your changes in detail -->

- The request methods add_data, has_data, were deprecated since 3.3.
- Use get() method instead of getheader() for HTTPMessage instance.

pr_title: Fix(#1071)Deprecation and SSL compatibility for python3.7
pr_body:
## Description

`ssl.PROTOCOL_SSLv23` deprecated since version 3.6: Use `PROTOCOL_TLS `instead.
Use `ssl.wrap_socket` in version python3.7  and `ssl.SSLSocket` in version python3.6 and below.

pr_title: Enhancement Plugin to test for Subdomain Takeover
pr_body:
<!--- Provide a general, concise summary of your changes in the Title above -->
Implement a plugin, which would check if the subdomains of a given domain are vulnerable for Subdomain Takeover.

## Description
<!--- Describe your changes in detail -->
`subdomain_takeover.sh`
The plugin first enumerates subdomain for a given domain. 
The enumeration of the subdomains takes place in three stages:-
1)It gathers subdomains from free online resources.
2)Enumeration using Amass.
3)Enumeration using Sublist3r.

Once the enumeration is done, the subdomain are sent to Subjack which checks if a subdomain is vulnerable to takeover based on certain fingerprints.

pr_title: Enhancement: Check for Public S3 Buckets
pr_body:
<!--- Provide a general, concise summary of your changes in the Title above -->
With Open S3 Buckets, sensitive files can be publicly accessed. 

## Description
<!--- Describe your changes in detail -->
`https://buckets.grayhatwarfare.com` is a free tool that lists open S3 buckets.

Since greyhatwarfare works best with Second Level Domain, we extract the second level domain and then pass it to the search query.
